The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Quarterly MF report

 Mumbai, Nov. 22 (PTI): Sebi has directed all mutual funds to dispatch the statement of accounts to unit holders once every quarter.

 MFs may henceforth dispatch statement of accounts every quarter ending March, June, September and December within 10 working days of the end of the respective quarter, a Sebi circular said.

 However, the first account statement shall be issued within 10 working days of the initial investment, Sebi said.

 Mutual funds, at present, dispatch the account statements to unit holders on monthly, quarterly or half-yearly basis. 




